<subSubSection id="828F6552E25FFFCEFF257564FD42EC20" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CA2A36D9E25FFFCEFF257564FD42EC20" blockId="5.[151,1074,1539,1658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">REMARKS: The male of this species is recognized by a retrolateral extension on the male bulb (Fig. 11), by a curved embolus gradually narrowing towards its sharply pointed apex (Figs 11-14), and by the TA carrying a lightly sclerotized prolateral process and a membranous retrolateral flange (Figs 12-14).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="828F6552E25CFFCDFF127384FEF3EB00" pageId="6" pageNumber="213" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="CA2A36D9E25CFFCDFF127384FEF3EB00" blockId="6.[136,1059,227,346]" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">
DISTRIBUTION: 
<collectingCountry id="B2827649E25CFFCDFEB27384FE06EAA0" box="[372,436,227,250]" name="Nepal" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="B2827649E25CFFCDFE2C7384FDFBEAA0" box="[490,585,227,250]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(new record, 
<figureCitation id="52AE2A5CE25CFFCDFD277384FC80EAA0" box="[737,818,227,250]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="13.[578,591,1438,1459]" captionTargetBox="[153,1067,227,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-47@13.[153,1067,226,1373]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIG. 32 Currently known Hersilia localities in Thailand." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5822828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5822828/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). As 
<taxonomicName id="0D954D5AE25CFFCDFCAD7383FC5FEAA1" authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1993" box="[875,1005,228,251]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sundaica">
<emphasis id="F8E1EACBE25CFFCDFCAD7383FC5FEAA1" box="[875,1005,228,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">H. sundaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species is apparently widely distributed. It was described from 
<collectingCountry id="B2827649E25CFFCDFCF27264FCC6EB40" box="[820,884,259,282]" name="Nepal" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and, as the first new record since its original description, is here documented from a forest in northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="B2827649E25CFFCDFF1C7224FE8EEB00" box="[218,316,323,346]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Thailand</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
